			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok I think I might have possibly found all of our problems with the combining process. I am making the assumption that we all know how to get the unfinished coif, righ? Well ok, after you have gotten the 3 red stackable scales needed in order to make the coif and have made it to a forge, put the coif in first(on the left hand column) then start putting the scales in one by one(that means unstacked to you who refuse to read :p) starting with the open slotin the right hand coulmn. Next put one in the 2nd left hand column. If you areb doing this correctly you shoould have one scale left. Put it, yep you guessed it, beside the last one in the right hand column. POOF works everytime, with no blacksmithing skillz whatsoever 5 time in a row. I think where most people are having the problem(and ive tested this thoroughly) is in the item placememnt when combining.. i.e all in one column or other funky placements. Hope this helps and good luck.
				</font>
